               <history rend="visible">
                  <origin>
                     
                     
                     
                     <origDate notBefore="1325" notAfter="1374">2nd and 3rd quarter of the 14th century</origDate>
                    
                     <origPlace>Spain, N. E. (Catalonia)</origPlace>
                 
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                                                          
                    <p>Coat of arms of the royal family of Leon and Castile: depicted (folios 1v, 4v, 5r, 156v).							</p>
                    <p>
                         <name type="person" role="owner">Daniyel Valentin</name> ?: inscribed with his name in a purchase note (folio 1r).
							</p>
                     <p>
                         <name type="person" role="owner">Bekhor Levi</name> of Constantinople, court physician of Sultan Abd el-Hamid (d. around 1899): see Sassoon, 1932. Probably based on the note which has been partially cut off (folio 88v).
							</p>
                      <p>
                        <name type="person" role="owner">David Solomon Sassoon</name> (b. 1880, d. 1942), book collector: in his collection (no. 1047); his book plate (inner front cover); his binding; his sale, Sotheby's Zurich 1975, lot 17.
							</p>
                                          
                     <p>Remains of a note in Hebrew (folio 88r, partially cut off).</p>
                  
                  
                  
                  </provenance>
                  
                  
                  
